Path: godot/classes/class_control.rst
Summary: This chunk describes the signals emitted by a Control node for events like gaining or losing focus, receiving GUI input, mouse entering or exiting, and changes to its size, minimum size, size flags, or theme.

Signals
Signal: focus_entered()
Emitted when the node gains focus.

Signal: focus_exited()
Emitted when the node loses focus.

Signal: gui_input(event: InputEvent)
Emitted when the node receives an InputEvent.

Signal: minimum_size_changed()
Emitted when the node's minimum size changes.

Signal: mouse_entered()
Emitted when the mouse cursor enters the control's (or any child control's) visible area, that is not occluded behind other Controls or Windows, provided its mouse_filter lets the event reach it and regardless if it's currently focused or not. Note: CanvasItem.z_index doesn't affect which Control receives the signal.

Signal: mouse_exited()
Emitted when the mouse cursor leaves the control's (and all child control's) visible area, that is not occluded behind other Controls or Windows, provided its mouse_filter lets the event reach it and regardless if it's currently focused or not. Note: CanvasItem.z_index doesn't affect which Control receives the signal. Note: If you want to check whether the mouse truly left the area, ignoring any top nodes, you can use code like this:
GDScript:
    func _on_mouse_exited():
        if not Rect2(Vector2(), size).has_point(get_local_mouse_position()):
            # Not hovering over area.

Signal: resized()
Emitted when the control changes size.

Signal: size_flags_changed()
Emitted when one of the size flags changes. See size_flags_horizontal and size_flags_vertical.

Signal: theme_changed()
Emitted when the NOTIFICATION_THEME_CHANGED notification is sent.
---CHUNK---
Document: Control
Path: godot/classes/class_control.rst
Summary: This chunk details the various enumerations for the Control class, including FocusMode, LayoutPreset, SizeFlags, MouseFilter, CursorShape, and others that define UI behavior, appearance, and layout.

Enumerations

enum FocusMode:
- FOCUS_NONE = 0: The node cannot grab focus. Use with focus_mode.
- FOCUS_CLICK = 1: The node can only grab focus on mouse clicks. Use with focus_mode.
- FOCUS_ALL = 2: The node can grab focus on mouse click, using the arrows and the Tab keys on the keyboard, or using the D-pad buttons on a gamepad. Use with focus_mode.
- FOCUS_ACCESSIBILITY = 3: The node can grab focus only when screen reader is active. Use with focus_mode.

enum FocusBehaviorRecursive:
- FOCUS_BEHAVIOR_INHERITED = 0: Inherits the focus_behavior_recursive from the parent control. If there is no parent control, this is the same as FOCUS_BEHAVIOR_ENABLED.
- FOCUS_BEHAVIOR_DISABLED = 1: Prevents the control from getting focused. get_focus_mode_with_override() will return FOCUS_NONE.
- FOCUS_BEHAVIOR_ENABLED = 2: Allows the control to be focused, depending on the focus_mode. This can be used to ignore the parent's focus_behavior_recursive. get_focus_mode_with_override() will return the focus_mode.

enum MouseBehaviorRecursive:
- MOUSE_BEHAVIOR_INHERITED = 0: Inherits the mouse_behavior_recursive from the parent control. If there is no parent control, this is the same as MOUSE_BEHAVIOR_ENABLED.
- MOUSE_BEHAVIOR_DISABLED = 1: Prevents the control from receiving mouse input. get_mouse_filter_with_override() will return MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE.
- MOUSE_BEHAVIOR_ENABLED = 2: Allows the control to receive mouse input, depending on the mouse_filter. This can be used to ignore the parent's mouse_behavior_recursive. get_mouse_filter_with_override() will return the mouse_filter.

enum CursorShape:
- CURSOR_ARROW = 0: Show the system's arrow mouse cursor.
- CURSOR_IBEAM = 1: Show the system's I-beam mouse cursor, used for text.
- CURSOR_POINTING_HAND = 2: Show the system's pointing hand mouse cursor.
- CURSOR_CROSS = 3: Show the system's cross mouse cursor.
- CURSOR_WAIT = 4: Show the system's wait mouse cursor (often an hourglass).
- CURSOR_BUSY = 5: Show the system's busy mouse cursor (often an arrow with a small hourglass).
- CURSOR_DRAG = 6: Show the system's drag mouse cursor (closed fist or cross), indicating an item is being dragged.
- CURSOR_CAN_DROP = 7: Show the system's drop mouse cursor (open hand), indicating an item can be dropped.
- CURSOR_FORBIDDEN = 8: Show the system's forbidden mouse cursor (crossed circle).
- CURSOR_VSIZE = 9: Show the system's vertical resize mouse cursor (double-headed vertical arrow).
- CURSOR_HSIZE = 10: Show the system's horizontal resize mouse cursor (double-headed horizontal arrow).
- CURSOR_BDIAGSIZE = 11: Show the system's window resize cursor (bottom-left to top-right double-headed arrow).
- CURSOR_FDIAGSIZE = 12: Show the system's window resize cursor (top-left to bottom-right double-headed arrow).
- CURSOR_MOVE = 13: Show the system's move mouse cursor (2 double-headed arrows at 90 degrees).
- CURSOR_VSPLIT = 14: Show the system's vertical split mouse cursor. On Windows, it's the same as CURSOR_VSIZE.
- CURSOR_HSPLIT = 15: Show the system's horizontal split mouse cursor. On Windows, it's the same as CURSOR_HSIZE.
- CURSOR_HELP = 16: Show the system's help mouse cursor (a question mark).

enum LayoutPreset:
- PRESET_TOP_LEFT = 0: Snap all 4 anchors to the top-left of the parent.
- PRESET_TOP_RIGHT = 1: Snap all 4 anchors to the top-right of the parent.
- PRESET_BOTTOM_LEFT = 2: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom-left of the parent.
- PRESET_BOTTOM_RIGHT = 3: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom-right of the parent.
- PRESET_CENTER_LEFT = 4: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the left edge of the parent.
- PRESET_CENTER_TOP = 5: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the top edge of the parent.
- PRESET_CENTER_RIGHT = 6: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the right edge of the parent.
- PRESET_CENTER_BOTTOM = 7: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the bottom edge of the parent.
- PRESET_CENTER = 8: Snap all 4 anchors to the center of the parent.
- PRESET_LEFT_WIDE = 9: Snap all 4 anchors to the left edge of the parent.
- PRESET_TOP_WIDE = 10: Snap all 4 anchors to the top edge of the parent.
- PRESET_RIGHT_WIDE = 11: Snap all 4 anchors to the right edge of the parent.
- PRESET_BOTTOM_WIDE = 12: Snap all 4 anchors to the bottom edge of the parent.
- PRESET_VCENTER_WIDE = 13: Snap all 4 anchors to a vertical line that cuts the parent in half.
- PRESET_HCENTER_WIDE = 14: Snap all 4 anchors to a horizontal line that cuts the parent in half.
- PRESET_FULL_RECT = 15: Snap all 4 anchors to the respective corners of the parent control.

enum LayoutPresetMode:
- PRESET_MODE_MINSIZE = 0: The control will be resized to its minimum size.
- PRESET_MODE_KEEP_WIDTH = 1: The control's width will not change.
- PRESET_MODE_KEEP_HEIGHT = 2: The control's height will not change.
- PRESET_MODE_KEEP_SIZE = 3: The control's size will not change.

flags SizeFlags:
- SIZE_SHRINK_BEGIN = 0: Tells the parent Container to align the node with its start (top or left). Note: Setting this flag is equal to not having any size flags.
- SIZE_FILL = 1: Tells the parent Container to expand the bounds of this node to fill all available space without pushing any other node.
- SIZE_EXPAND = 2: Tells the parent Container to let this node take all available space on an axis. If multiple nodes expand, they share space based on size_flags_stretch_ratio.
- SIZE_EXPAND_FILL = 3: Sets the node's size flags to both fill and expand.
- SIZE_SHRINK_CENTER = 4: Tells the parent Container to center the node in the available space.
- SIZE_SHRINK_END = 8: Tells the parent Container to align the node with its end (bottom or right).

enum MouseFilter:
- MOUSE_FILTER_STOP = 0: The control receives mouse events via _gui_input() and the mouse_entered/mouse_exited signals. Events are marked as handled and do not propagate further.
- MOUSE_FILTER_PASS = 1: The control receives mouse events. If not handled, the event propagates up to its parent. This allows signals to fire in all controls the event reaches.
- MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE = 2: The control does not receive any mouse input events or signals. This does not block other controls. Note: If the control has received mouse_entered but not mouse_exited, changing the mouse_filter to MOUSE_FILTER_IGNORE will cause mouse_exited to be emitted.

enum GrowDirection:
- GROW_DIRECTION_BEGIN = 0: The control will grow to the left or top if its minimum size increases.
- GROW_DIRECTION_END = 1: The control will grow to the right or bottom if its minimum size increases.
- GROW_DIRECTION_BOTH = 2: The control will grow in both directions equally if its minimum size increases.

enum Anchor:
- ANCHOR_BEGIN = 0: Snaps an anchor side to the origin of the node's Rect (top left).
- ANCHOR_END = 1: Snaps an anchor side to the end of the node's Rect (bottom right).

enum LayoutDirection:
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_INHERITED = 0: Automatic layout direction, determined from the parent control.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_APPLICATION_LOCALE = 1: Automatic layout direction, determined from the current locale. Uses RTL for languages like Arabic and Hebrew if a valid translation is loaded.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_LTR = 2: Left-to-right layout direction.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_RTL = 3: Right-to-left layout direction.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_SYSTEM_LOCALE = 4: Automatic layout direction, determined from the system locale.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_MAX = 5: Represents the size of the LayoutDirection enum.
- LAYOUT_DIRECTION_LOCALE = 1: Deprecated. Use LAYOUT_DIRECTION_APPLICATION_LOCALE instead.

enum TextDirection:
- TEXT_DIRECTION_INHERITED = 3: Text writing direction is the same as layout direction.
- TEXT_DIRECTION_AUTO = 0: Automatic text writing direction, determined from the current locale and text content.
- TEXT_DIRECTION_LTR = 1: Left-to-right text writing direction.
- TEXT_DIRECTION_RTL = 2: Right-to-left text writing direction.
---CHUNK---
